.TH "hfi1_rcd_get_by_index_safe" 9 "hfi1_rcd_get_by_index_safe" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hfi1_rcd_get_by_index_safe \- validate the ctxt index before accessing the array
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct hfi1_ctxtdata *" hfi1_rcd_get_by_index_safe
.BI "(struct hfi1_devdata *dd "  ","
.BI "u16 ctxt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dd" 12
pointer to a valid devdata structure
.IP "ctxt" 12
the index of an possilbe rcd
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is a wrapper for \fBhfi1_rcd_get_by_index\fP to validate that the given
ctxt index is valid.

The caller is responsible for making the \fB_put\fP.
